cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with a problem of private estimation of the mean of a Gaussian distribution, which involves differential privacy and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the privacy aspect of the problem, which may fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
